<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,1412,2016]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1592,1619]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Membranous parts of integument with fine papillae. Genital field (
<figureCitation box="[1087,1192,1592,1620]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1516,1541]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,265,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[151,1436,265,1496]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 25. Family Teratothyadidae, Teratothyas (s. str.) aucta (MD 084), female. a. idiosoma, venter; b. genital field; c. dorsocentral sclerite 2; d. chelicera; e. gnathosoma lateral; f. palp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613352/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 25 b</figureCitation>
) with short acetabula (L Ac-1-3, 30–48, 44–58, 33–41, relative L Ac-1, 19–28, Ac-2, 27–32 % genital flap); Ac-2/-3 distinctly separated from each other; medial genital flap margins in posterior 3/4 straight. An unpaired medial platelet between genital field and excretory plate (
<figureCitation box="[436,537,1700,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1516,1541]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,265,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[151,1436,265,1496]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 25. Family Teratothyadidae, Teratothyas (s. str.) aucta (MD 084), female. a. idiosoma, venter; b. genital field; c. dorsocentral sclerite 2; d. chelicera; e. gnathosoma lateral; f. palp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613352/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 25 a</figureCitation>
). Leg claws with rounded basal blade. Gnathosoma (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1224,1700,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1516,1541]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,265,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[151,1436,265,1496]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 25. Family Teratothyadidae, Teratothyas (s. str.) aucta (MD 084), female. a. idiosoma, venter; b. genital field; c. dorsocentral sclerite 2; d. chelicera; e. gnathosoma lateral; f. palp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613352/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 25 e</figureCitation>
) basal part extend- ed, proximodorsal apodeme barely developed. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[744,843,1736,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1516,1541]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,265,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[151,1436,265,1496]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 25. Family Teratothyadidae, Teratothyas (s. str.) aucta (MD 084), female. a. idiosoma, venter; b. genital field; c. dorsocentral sclerite 2; d. chelicera; e. gnathosoma lateral; f. palp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613352/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 25 f</figureCitation>
) short, P-4 very stout (L/H ratio 3.7–4.1), maximum H in distal part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,1412,2016]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1808,1835]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Description:</emphasis>
Idiosoma rather slender. Membranous parts of integument with fine (occasionally barely visible) papillae. Pores of idiosoma sclerites rather large (&lt;10 per transect on dorsocentralia), inner trabecular structures poorly developed, only in dorsolateral and posteroventral plates. Glandularia surrounded by a finely porose collar (
<figureCitation box="[160,262,1916,1943]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1516,1541]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,265,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[151,1436,265,1496]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 25. Family Teratothyadidae, Teratothyas (s. str.) aucta (MD 084), female. a. idiosoma, venter; b. genital field; c. dorsocentral sclerite 2; d. chelicera; e. gnathosoma lateral; f. palp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613352/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 25 c</figureCitation>
). Legs relatively slender, claws with a projecting, rounded basal blade.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,1412,2016]" lastBlockId="51.[151,1437,153,1799]" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Unpaired sclerite between coxal margins slender, genital field not situated in a genital bay (Cx-IV with slightly convex posteromedial margin, medial projections weakly developed or absent); genital flaps with straight medial, and equally rounded lateral margins (secondary sclerite fringe narrow or absent), bearing about 13 pairs of medial, and 7 pairs of posterior setae. Ac-1 very small, in a short bay of concave genital flap margin (bordering setae here stronger than the posterior, pinnate), Ac-2 and -3 also short, away from each other. Plates embracing posterolateral genital field margin small, subtriangular, with concave anterior margin; between their posteromedial margins and the excretory pore plate an unpaired platelet.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,153,1799]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Gnathosoma (
<figureCitation box="[358,463,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1516,1541]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,265,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[151,1436,265,1496]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 25. Family Teratothyadidae, Teratothyas (s. str.) aucta (MD 084), female. a. idiosoma, venter; b. genital field; c. dorsocentral sclerite 2; d. chelicera; e. gnathosoma lateral; f. palp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613352/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 25 e</figureCitation>
) posterior to rostrum with a steeply S-shaped ventral margin, its proximal part elongated, with a prominent proximoventral apodeme, proximodorsal apodemes weakly developed as small, rounded projections. Chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[414,519,404,432]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1516,1541]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,265,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[151,1436,265,1496]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 25. Family Teratothyadidae, Teratothyas (s. str.) aucta (MD 084), female. a. idiosoma, venter; b. genital field; c. dorsocentral sclerite 2; d. chelicera; e. gnathosoma lateral; f. palp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613352/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 25 d</figureCitation>
) relatively stout, L/H 5.6–7.5, basal segment/claw 0.9–1.1. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[1264,1364,404,432]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1516,1541]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,265,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[151,1436,265,1496]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 25. Family Teratothyadidae, Teratothyas (s. str.) aucta (MD 084), female. a. idiosoma, venter; b. genital field; c. dorsocentral sclerite 2; d. chelicera; e. gnathosoma lateral; f. palp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613352/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 25 f</figureCitation>
) short and stout, P-1 with one pennate dorsal seta; P-2 and -3 distally expanding, P-2 bearing four fine dorsal and the two typical strong, pennate, distoventral setae, P-3 with three simple dorsal setae; P-4 short, with slightly undulating ventral and dorsal margins, maximum H in centre or distal part, bearing 4 fine, hair-like setae, one dorsally in the proximal half, three flanking P-5-insertion, distal margin forming an obtuse angle at the insertion of the pointed distolateral peg seta; P-5 not particularly slender, with little curved claws.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,153,1799]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Measurements: Male: Idiosoma L/W 640/430; coxal field L/W 420/380; Cx-I+II L/W 220/180; Cx-III+IV L/W 295/170; genital field L/W 145/140; maximum diameter Ac-1, 35, Ac-2, 45, Ac-3, 41; ejaculatory complex L/W 155/50; gnathosoma L/W 160/85; chelicera total L 298, basal segment/claw 1.06, L/H 7,5; Palp partly damaged; L, L/H ratio, palp segments: P-3, 43, 1.55; P-4, 93, 4.1; P-5, 35, 3.1; L ratio P-3/-4, 0.46. Leg segments L/H, L/H ratio: I-L-2, 65, 1.63; I-L-3, 63, 1.56; I-L-4, 83, 2.36; I-L-5, 85, 2.43; I-L-6, 98, 2.67; claw L 30. II-L-2, 80, 2.13; II-L-3, 70, 1.87; II-L-4, 105, 2.80; II-L-5, 105, 3.50; II-L-6, 113, 3.08; claw L 30. III-L-2, 63, 1.79; III-L-3, 60, 1.60; III-L- 4, 100, 2.86; III-L-5, 103, 3.73; III-L-6, 113, 3.75; claw L 33. IV-L-2, 80, 2.13; IV-L-3, 90, 2.40; IV-L-4, 150, 4.00; IV-L-5, 145, 4.46; IV-L-6, 125, 4.17; claw L 43. Total L segments 2–6: I-L, 393; II-L, 473; III-L, 438; IV-L, 590.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,153,1799]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Female: Idiosoma L/W 840–1050/530–650; coxal field L/W 470–580/420–560; Cx-I+II L/W 250–340/165– 210; Cx-III+IV L/W 330–390/210–280; genital field L/W 160–180/160–190; maximum diameter Ac-1, 30–48, Ac-2, 44–58, Ac-3, 33–40; gnathosoma L 190–230; chelicera total L 300–350, basal segment/claw 0.89–1.06, L/H 5.56–7,50; Palp total L 264–303; L, L/H ratio, relative L [% total L] palp segments: P-1, 33–50, 1.00–1.46, 12–17; P-2, 53–68, 1.62–2.13, 20–22; P-3, 48–50, 1.43–1.73, 17–18; P-4, 93–100, 3.33–3.95, 32–37; P-5, 33–36, 2.60– 2.90, 12–13; L ratio P-2/-3, 1.11–1.36; P-2/-4, 0.53–0.68; P-3/-4, 0.48–0.54. Leg segments L/H, L/H ratio: I-L-2, 95, 1.90; I-L-3, 85, 1.79; I-L-4, 110, 2.44; I-L-5, 118, 2.94; I-L-6, 120, 2.82; claw L 35. II-L-2, 105, 1.91; II-L-3, 90, 1.80; II-L-4, 150, 3.16; II-L-5, 150, 3.75; II-L-6, 140, 2.50; claw L 43. III-L-2, 90, 2.00; III-L-3, 75, 1.67; III-L-4, 135, 3.00; III-L-5, 140, 3.84; III-L-6, 130, 2.74; claw L 40. IV-L-2, 113, 2.25; IV-L-3, 115, 2.30; IV-L-4, 200, 4.44; IV-L-5, 175, 4.12; IV-L-6, 190, 4.22; claw L 45. Total L segments 2-6: I-L, 528; II-L, 635; III-L, 570; IV-L, 793.</paragraph>
